use # symbol to start writing a comment.
it extends up to the newline character.
comments are for programmers to notify the programmers idea of what the code is for.
comments can be placed at the end of a line, and Python will ignore the rest of the line.
a comment does not have to be text that explains the code, it can also be used to prevent Python from executing order.

Example:
#print("Hello, World") 
print("Cheers, Mate!")
